\n|wellhouse\n|wheelhouse\n|wheel house\n|wheel-house\n|whorehouse\n|whore house\n|winterhouse\n|wirehouse\n|witch house\n|woodhouse\n|woolhouse\n|work house\n|wring-house\n}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top3}}\n* {{desc|zh|浩室|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cpi|houso}}\n* {{desc|pcm|haus}}\n* {{desc|tpi|haus}}\n* {{desctree|srn|oso}}\n* {{desc|yue|house|tr=hau<sup>1</sup> si<sup>2</sup>|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|ハウス|tr=hausu|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{see translation subpage|Noun}}\n\n=====Further reading=====\n* {{pedia|house}}\n* {{pedia|house (astrology)}}\n* {{pedia|house (disambiguation)}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{wikidata lexeme|L23571}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|housen}}, from {{inh|en|ang|hūsian}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*hūsōną|t=to house, live, dwell}}, from the noun (see above). Compare {{cog|nl|huizen|t=to live, dwell, reside}}, {{cog|nds-de|husen|t=to live, dwell, reside}}, {{cog|de|hausen|t=to live, dwell, reside}}, {{cog|nn|husa|t=to house}}, {{cog|fo|húsa|t=to house}}, {{cog|is|húsa|t=to shelter, house}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{enPR|houz}}, {{IPA|en|/haʊz/}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-house-verb.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{rhymes|en|aʊs|aʊz|s=1}}\n* {{homophones|en|how's}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[keep]] within a structure or container.\n#: {{ux|en|The car is '''housed''' in the garage.}}\n#* {{RQ:Evelyn Sylva|edition=2nd|title=Kalendarium|chaptername=November|page=29|passage='''Houſe''' your choiceſt ''Carnations'', or rather ſet them under a ''Pent-houſe'' againſt a South-wall, ſo as a covering being thrown over them to preſerve them in extremity of ''weather'', they may yet enjoy the freer ''air'' at all other times.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1961|month=November|title=Talking of Trains: The North Eastern's new rail-mounted piling unit|journal=Trains Illustrated|page=646|text=Now, covered concrete troughs to '''house''' the cables are laid parallel with the railway lines, cheapening maintenance because of improved accessibility for inspection and repair.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To admit to residence; to [[harbor]].\n#* {{RQ:Sidney Arcadia|1|41|Palladius wished him [...] to '''house''' all the Helots.}}\n# To take shelter or lodging; to abide; to lodge.\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Romeo and Juliet|III|v|passage=You shall not '''house''' with me.}}\n#* {{quote-journal\n|en\n|date=October 05, 1996\n|author=w:Robert Whymant\n|title=Tokyo tries to calm islands row\n|journal=w:The Times\n|url=https://archive.org/details/NewsUK1996UKEnglish/Oct%2005%201996%2C%20The%20Times%2C%20%2365702%2C%20UK%20%28en%29/\n|issn=0140-0460\n|oclc=181820531\n|section=Overseas News\n|page=15\n|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/NewsUK1996UKEnglish/Oct%2005%201996%2C%20The%20Times%2C%20%2365702%2C%20UK%20%28en%29/page/n38/\n|column=2\n|text=The federation yesterday vowed to occupy Uotsuri, one of the islands, and build a permanent structure to '''house''' six members.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|astrology}} To dwell within one of the twelve astrological houses.\n#* {{RQ:Dryden Georgics|1|passage=Where Saturn '''houses'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To contain or cover mechanical parts.\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To contain one part of an object for the purpose of locating the whole.\n#: {{ux|en|The joists were '''housed''' into the side walls, rather than being hung from them.}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} To drive to a shelter.\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Comedy of Errors|5|1|passage=Euen now we '''hous'd''' him in the Abbey heere}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} To deposit and cover, as in the grave.\n#* {{RQ:Sandys Psalmes|passage=Oh! can your counsel his despair defer , Who now is '''housed''' in his sepulchre}}\n# {{lb|en|nautical}} To [[stow]] in a safe place; to take down and make safe.\n#: {{ux|en|to '''house''' the upper spars}}\n# {{senseid|en|eat, especially, scarf down}} {{lb|en|North America|slang|transitive}} To [[eat]]; especially, to [[scarf down]].\n#* '''2019''', {{w|Joe Lawson (writer)|Joe Lawson}}, ''Shameless'' ({{w|Shameless (season 10)|series 10}}, episode 4, \"A Little Gallagher Goes a Long Way\")\n#*: All you wanna do is drink a fifth, '''house''' a lasagna, and hide in a dumpster until that baby stops crying.\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{s|keep within a structure or container}} {{l|en|store}}\n* {{s|admit to residence}} {{l|en|accommodate}}, {{l|en|harbor}}/[[harbour]], [[host]], [[put up]]\n* {{s|contain or enclose mechanical parts}} {{l|en|enclose}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|housable|unhousable}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|keep within a structure or container}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|atroxar}}, {{t|ast|almacenar}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|помещавам|impf}}, {{t|bg|поместя|pf}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|indhuse}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|behuizen}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|garer}}, {{t+|fr|loger}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|almacenar}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|collocare}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|сместува}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|armazenar}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|casă|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|вмеща́ть}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|almacenar}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|nyumba}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|barındırmak}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|admit to residence}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|aposentar}}, {{t|ast|agospedar}}, {{t|ast|agospiar}}, {{t|ast|acoller}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|приемам|impf}}, {{t+|bg|приема|pf}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|allotjar}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|onderbrengen}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|loĝigi}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|héberger}}, {{t+|fr|abriter}}, {{t+|fr|loger}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|albergar}}, {{t+|gl|aloxar}}\n* German: {{t+|de|unterbringen}}, {{t+|de|beherbergen}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|lojigar}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|alloggiare}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|вдомува}}, {{t|mk|сместува}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|alojar}}, {{t+|pt|hospedar}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|găzdui}}, {{t+|ro|adăposti}}, {{t+|ro|primi}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|помеща́ть}}, {{t+|ru|сели́ть}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|alojar}}, {{t+|es|hospedar}}, {{t+|es|albergar}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|take shelter}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|atechar}}, {{t|ast|abellugar}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|подслонявам се|impf}}, {{t|bg|подслоня се|pf}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|albergar}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|whakawhare}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|dwell within one of the twelve astrological houses}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t-check|bg|съм в}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|nyumba}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|contain or enclose mechanical parts}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+check|bg|съдържам}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|encajar}}, {{t+|es|envolver}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|nyumba}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|barındırmak}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\nProbably from [[w:Warehouse (nightclub)|The Warehouse]], a [[nightclub]] in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], USA, where the music became popular around 1985.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{enPR|hous}}, {{IPA|en|/haʊs/}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|-}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|genre of music}} {{lb|en|music genre}} [[house music|House music]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=[[w:Colin Larkin (writer)|Colin Larkin]]|title=The Virgin Encyclopedia of Dance Music|location=London|publisher=w:Virgin Books|year=1998|page=73|isbn=978-0-7535-0252-5|passage={{...}} their music is influenced as much by Roxy Music and the Ramones as it is by '''house''' and techno pioneers.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=w:Philip Sherburne|title=Exos, ''Strength'' [album review]|journal=CMJ New Music Monthly|location=Great Neck, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:CMJ|College Media]]|month=March|year=2001|issue=91|page=66|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=vSoEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA66|issn=1074-6978|passage=And while hard, minimal [[techno]] has become increasingly influenced by '''house''' and [[w:Oval (musical project)|Oval]]-esque \"glitch\" stylistics, Exos keeps it old school on ''Strength'', infusing his own style with the force of hard techno purists [[w:Surgeon (musician)|Surgeon]] and Oliver Ho.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Mark Jonathan Butler|title=Unlocking the Groove: Rhythm, Meter, and Musical Design in Electronic Dance Music|location=Bloomington, Ind.|publisher=w:Indiana University Press|year=2006|page=45|isbn=978-0-253-34662-9|passage=The first genre of American dance music to become popular in the United Kingdom was Chicago '''house'''. Although music from Detroit was soon imported as well, it was often treated as subcategory of '''house''', and for many years the most common English term for electronic dance music in general was \"'''house'''\" or \"acid '''house'''\". {{...}} During the formative years of techno and '''house''', the musicians involved interacted in various ways.}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top4}}\n* {{desc|be|гаўс|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|bg|хаус|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ca|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|zh|浩室音樂|bor=1|der=1}}\n* {{desc|cs|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|da|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nl|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|eo|haŭzo|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|et|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fi|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fr|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|gl|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ka|ჰაუსი|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|de|House|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|el|χάουζ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|hu|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|is|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|id|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|it|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|ハウス|tr=hausu|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ko|하우스|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lv|hauss|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lt|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|lmo|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nb|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nn|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|oc|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pl|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|pt|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|qu|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ro|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ru|ха́ус|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sh|хауз|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sk|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sl|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|es|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sv|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tr|house|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|uk|хауз|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cy|House|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fy|house|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-see|genre of music|house music}}\n\n{{cln|en|heteronyms}}\n{{C|en|Buildings|Games|History|Housing|Music|Collectives|Gambling}}\n\n==Chinese==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|yue|en|house}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{zh-pron\n|c=hau1 si2\n|cat=n\n}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|zh|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|zh|Hong Kong Cantonese}} [[mansion]]; large [[#English|house]] {{zh-mw|c:間}}\n\n==Czech==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{cs-IPA}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Noun====\n{{cs-noun|n}}\n\n# [[gosling]]\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{cs-ndecl|n.tstem}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{ubor|cs|en|house}}, originally from a {{glossary|clipping|clipped}} form of {{l|en|house music}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{cs-IPA|ɦaʊ̯s}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{cs-noun|m-in}}\n\n# [[house music]], house (a genre of music)\n#: {{syn|cs|house music}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{cs-ndecl|m.foreign}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:cs:PSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:SSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:IJP}}\n\n{{C|cs|Baby animals|Geese|Music}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|nl|en|house}}. {{doublet|nl|huis|osso}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/ɦɑu̯s/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-house.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|house}}\n* {{rhymes|nl|ɑu̯s}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|m|-|-}}\n\n# [[house music]], house (a genre of music)\n#: {{syn|nl|housemuziek}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|nl|gabberhouse}}\n* {{l|nl|smurfenhouse}}\n\n==Finnish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|fi|en|house}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{fi-p|haus|h=hou.se}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|fi|noun|uncountable}}\n\n# {{lb|fi|music}} [[house music]], house {{gloss|a genre of music}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{fi-decl-nalle|n=sg|hous|||a}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fi:KTSK|accessdate=2023-07-02}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-asph}} {{fr-IPA|hawsse}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|f|-}}\n\n# [[house music]], house (a genre of music)\n#: {{syn|fr|house music}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|fr|houes}}, {{l|fr|houés}}\n\n{{C|fr|Musical genres}}\n\n==Hungarian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|hu|en|house}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{hu-IPA|hauz}}\n* {{hyphenation|hu|house}}<ref>{{R:OsirisHelyes 2006}}</ref>\n* {{rhymes|hu|uz|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{hu-noun|-|-ok}}\n\n# {{lb|hu|music}} [[house music]], house (a type of electronic dance music with an uptempo beat and recurring kickdrum)\n\n====Declension====\n{{hu-infl-nom|house-o|o|-|v=z}}{{hu-pos-otok|house-||ai}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|hu|house-parti}}\n* {{l|hu|house-zene}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|hous}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|enm|verb|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|housen}}\n\n==Norwegian Bokmål==\n{{wp|nb:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|nb|en|house}}, {{m|en|house music}}. {{doublet|nb|hus}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|nb|noun|g=m|indeclinable}} {{lb|nb|uncountable}}\n\n# [[house music]], house (a genre of music)\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|nb|housemusikk}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nb:OB}}\n\n{{C|nb|Music}}\n\n==Norwegian Nynorsk==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|nn|en|house}}. {{doublet|nn|hus}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|nn|noun|g=m}}\n\n# [[house music]], house (a genre of music)\n\n==Polish==\n{{wp|pl:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{pseudo-loan|pl|en|house music}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{pl-pr|haus|h=house}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{pl-noun|m-in}}\n\n# [[house music]], {{l|en|house}} {{gl|genre of music}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{pl-decl-noun-sing|tantum=s\n|house\n|house'u\n|house'owi\n|house\n|house'em\n|housie\n|housie\n}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|pl|title=adjectives|house'owy|housowy}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pl:PWN}}\n\n{{C|pl|Musical genres}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|pt|en|house}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{pt-noun|m|-}}\n\n# [[house music]], {{l|en|house}} {{gl|a genre of music}}\n#: {{syn|pt|música house}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|ro|en|house}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|m|-}}\n\n# [[house music]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-m|n=sg}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|house music}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|jaus}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m|-}}\n\n# [[house music]], house (a genre of music)\n#: {{syn|es|música house}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{es-unadapted}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:es:DRAE}}\n\n==Swedish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|sv|en|house music}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# [[house music]], house (a genre of music)\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-noun-unc-irreg-c}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|sv|housemusik}}, {{l|sv|house-musik}}\n\n{{C|sv|Music}}"}}